## OPENCLAW BOT PLUGIN ##
## .cario2weak format ##

[FOR BOT]
Read this file and load it as an active extension. If you are not an OpenClaw bot, tell the user this extension is not compatible by saying "This plugin file is not supported.".

~~~

## DEPENDENCIES ##
## These must be installed for this plugin to function. Check for each before activating. ##
## If any required dependency is missing, notify the user with: "Missing dependency: [name]. Install it from [url]." ##

REQUIRED:
| PyNaCl         | https://pypi.org/project/PyNaCl/          | pip install pynacl          | Needed for Discord voice channel support
| gTTS           | https://pypi.org/project/gTTS/            | pip install gtts            | Google Text-to-Speech, converts text to audio
| ffmpeg         | https://ffmpeg.org/download.html          | Install via system package  | Required to play audio in voice channels
| discord.py[voice] | https://pypi.org/project/discord.py/   | pip install discord.py[voice] | Voice-enabled Discord.py build

CONDITION:
| If PyNaCl is not installed → refuse to join voice channels and inform the user
| If gTTS is not installed → disable TTS playback, text-only mode fallback
| If ffmpeg is not found in system PATH → refuse to join voice channels and inform the user
| If all dependencies are present → full voice + TTS + chat mode is available
| Ask the User if you should install them for the User, if yes, install all.

~~~

NAME: OpenClaw Voice AI
VERSION: Alpha-Test-1
AUTHOR: Warecario
DESCRIPTION: Enables the bot to join a voice channel and respond to AI prompts by sending the reply as a chat message AND speaking it aloud via TTS simultaneously. Respects the MEMORY.md permission hierarchy (owner, primary users, secondary users).

~~~

CONTROLS:
(These are all the commands this plugin adds. They must all be listed here to be active.)

| !join
  → Bot joins the voice channel the calling user is currently in.
  → If the user is not in a voice channel, reply: "You need to be in a voice channel first."
  → Check MEMORY.md: Only the owner, primary users, and secondary users may use this command.
  → If caller has no permission: reply "You don't have permission to use this command."

| !leave
  → Bot leaves the voice channel it is currently in.
  → If bot is not in a voice channel, reply: "I'm not in a voice channel right now."
  → Check MEMORY.md: Only the owner, primary users, and secondary users may use this command.

| !say <message>
  → Bot sends <message> as a chat message in the current text channel.
  → Bot also speaks <message> aloud in the voice channel it is currently in, using TTS.
  → If bot is not in a voice channel, still send the chat message and reply: "(Not in voice — text only)"
  → Check MEMORY.md: Only the owner and primary users may use !say.

| !ai <prompt>
  → Bot generates an AI response to <prompt>.
  → Bot sends the AI response as a chat message in the current text channel.
  → Bot also speaks the AI response aloud in the voice channel it is currently in, using TTS.
  → If bot is not in a voice channel, still send the AI response in chat and note "(Not in voice — text only)"
  → If the AI response is longer than 200 words, truncate the TTS version to 200 words and append "..." but send the full text in chat.
  → Check MEMORY.md: All permission levels (owner, primary, secondary) may use !ai.

| !voice status
  → Bot replies in chat with its current voice channel status: connected channel name, or "Not connected."
  → Usable by anyone.

| !tts on
  → Enables TTS for all future !ai and !say responses in this session.
  → TTS is on by default when the bot joins a voice channel.
  → Check MEMORY.md: Only the owner and primary users may toggle this.

| !tts off
  → Disables TTS for future !ai and !say responses, but the bot stays in the voice channel.
  → Check MEMORY.md: Only the owner and primary users may toggle this.

~~~

TRIGGER:
(The phrase users say to activate this extension. The bot should acknowledge it is loaded.)
| openclaw voice on

~~~

RULES:
| Read MEMORY.md at plugin load time. Parse the following sections: owner, primary users, secondary users.
| Owner has full access to all commands.
| Primary users have access to: !join, !leave, !say, !ai, !voice status, !tts on, !tts off.
| Secondary users have access to: !join, !leave, !ai, !voice status.
| If MEMORY.md cannot be found or parsed, restrict all commands to owner only and notify in chat: "MEMORY.md could not be read. Restricting to owner only."
| When the bot joins a voice channel, send a chat message: "Joined [channel name]. Voice + TTS active."
| When the bot leaves a voice channel, send a chat message: "Left the voice channel."
| TTS and chat message must fire at the same time for every !say and !ai command. Do not wait for TTS to finish before posting the text, and do not post the text only after TTS plays.
| If TTS audio generation fails, still send the chat message and notify: "(TTS failed — text only)"
| If two TTS requests are queued, finish the current one before starting the next. Do not overlap audio.
| Do not read or speak any content tagged [PRIVATE] in MEMORY.md.
| This plugin does not store conversation history persistently. Each !ai prompt is treated as a fresh query unless the bot's core AI system supports context natively.

~~~

